  "doc_id": "638",
  "text": "The genetic studies previously carried out by our team have shown that the Champagne and Térèse lines differ in their response to cold. Following a period of acclimation, the Ch line becomes tolerant to frost while Te remains sensitive [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . This present study aims to provide molecular elements to explain the cold responses in pea. The statistical treatments of the RNA-seq data of 73,225 unigenes led us to distinguish 4981 DEGs, divided into three main sets according to their expression patterns. The analysis of these genes, their modulation of expression, and their affiliation to metabolic pathways has allowed us to enrich our knowledge on the behavior of these two lines regarding their response to cold.",
